1
00:00:37,558 --> 00:00:39,185
EPISODE 6

2
00:00:46,609 --> 00:00:50,696
- Wait, that one's not expired yet.
- Oh. Right.

3
00:00:51,947 --> 00:00:53,908
It's not like you to make such a mistake.

4
00:00:54,909 --> 00:00:59,246
Did something happen yesterday
with the CCTV footage?

5
00:01:03,584 --> 00:01:06,796
Yesterday, I met Jeong Ho-myeong.

6
00:01:07,630 --> 00:01:09,548
You met Jeong Ho-myeong?

7
00:01:09,632 --> 00:01:10,675
Right.

8
00:01:11,884 --> 00:01:16,931
But that guy didn't just know me.
He knows a lot about you, too.

9
00:01:18,015 --> 00:01:19,266
Did he?

10
00:01:19,975 --> 00:01:22,269
- He said he knew me?
- Yeah.

11
00:01:23,104 --> 00:01:26,023
And not just our faces.

12
00:01:27,149 --> 00:01:29,777
He even knows why we came
to Yeongseon Island ten years ago.

13
00:01:30,528 --> 00:01:31,862
He knows everything about us.

14
00:01:37,785 --> 00:01:38,828
Okay, look.

15
00:01:39,370 --> 00:01:41,330
- There's something I need to tell you.
- Go on.

16
00:01:59,014 --> 00:02:00,558
So, what's good here?

17
00:02:00,683 --> 00:02:01,892
Best we've got are lunch boxes.

18
00:02:01,976 --> 00:02:03,644
What did you expect? Chinese food?

19
00:02:03,728 --> 00:02:04,812
What do you say?

20
00:02:04,895 --> 00:02:07,273
There's a new one.
Want me to shove it down your throat?

21
00:02:07,356 --> 00:02:08,524
Ah.

22
00:02:08,607 --> 00:02:11,277
I didn't come for a lunch box.
I came to talk.

23
00:02:11,360 --> 00:02:13,863
You threw me to the curb,
and now you want to talk?

24
00:02:13,946 --> 00:02:16,157
It's not like we're carpooling buddies,
is it?

25
00:02:16,782 --> 00:02:18,534
Cut the crap and listen up.

26
00:02:18,617 --> 00:02:21,912
I'm about to make you
an offer you can't refuse.

27
00:02:23,831 --> 00:02:26,709
I've decided to be generous.

28
00:02:28,794 --> 00:02:30,379
I'll take you in.

29
00:02:32,548 --> 00:02:33,549
What?

30
00:02:33,632 --> 00:02:36,385
Do as I say,
and I'll help you get your revenge.

31
00:02:38,554 --> 00:02:40,848
What the hell are you barking about?

32
00:02:43,267 --> 00:02:47,104
Speaking of barking,
you're pretty good at it.

33
00:02:48,773 --> 00:02:49,774
Mr. Jeong!

34
00:02:51,567 --> 00:02:52,818
How did you get that?

35
00:02:54,653 --> 00:02:57,656
Anyway, you must have realized
you can't take on Yoo In-gu alone.

36
00:02:57,740 --> 00:03:00,993
So you sought another way,
trying to meet Prosecutor Gang yesterday.

37
00:03:01,076 --> 00:03:04,580
But that route's a dead end,
so you have no options now, do you?

38
00:03:04,663 --> 00:03:06,707
You think you know everything, don't you?

39
00:03:06,791 --> 00:03:08,042
I'll never work with you!

40
00:03:08,125 --> 00:03:10,628
You'll be working for me, not with me.

41
00:03:10,711 --> 00:03:11,879
Let's just get that straight.

42
00:03:14,048 --> 00:03:17,968
I bet Gong-bok here thinks differently.

43
00:03:27,144 --> 00:03:29,063
He does have a point.

44
00:03:29,146 --> 00:03:31,565
Maybe you should think it over.

45
00:03:32,525 --> 00:03:33,526
Ma Gong-bok.

46
00:03:33,984 --> 00:03:35,945
You can't just show up out of nowhere!

47
00:03:36,028 --> 00:03:39,114
- You should have let me know!
- I just did.

48
00:03:39,573 --> 00:03:42,159
Anyway, I've said my piece.
The rest is up to you two.

49
00:03:42,243 --> 00:03:43,953
The deadline is midnight tonight.

50
00:03:44,036 --> 00:03:46,664
If you're one minute late, the deal's off.

51
00:03:46,747 --> 00:03:47,748
Choose wisely.

52
00:03:54,213 --> 00:03:56,173
- Did you betray me?
- Betray you?

53
00:03:56,674 --> 00:03:59,176
Boss,
is that all the faith you have in me?

54
00:03:59,260 --> 00:04:00,511
Mr. Jeong, huh?

55
00:04:01,345 --> 00:04:03,889
- You looked pretty chummy.
- We're not.

56
00:04:04,557 --> 00:04:05,975
I was going to tell you.

57
00:04:06,058 --> 00:04:07,893
Recently, I got to know Mr. Jeong...

58
00:04:11,647 --> 00:04:15,109
I mean, Jeong Ho-myeong
looking into Yoo In-gu.

59
00:04:15,192 --> 00:04:16,193
Yoo In-gu?

60
00:04:16,986 --> 00:04:18,529
Didn't you promise to move on?

61
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:24,618
Boss, can you really do that?

62
00:04:26,245 --> 00:04:28,122
The betrayal ten years ago?

63
00:04:28,747 --> 00:04:30,708
And the humiliation we just suffered?

64
00:04:31,542 --> 00:04:32,960
I can't forget a single thing.

65
00:04:33,669 --> 00:04:35,546
I still hear that asshole's voice
in my sleep.

66
00:04:35,629 --> 00:04:38,591
You should have told me. I'm your boss.

67
00:04:38,674 --> 00:04:40,050
And if I had?

68
00:04:41,802 --> 00:04:44,263
Boss, do you have the guts
to give up this store?

69
00:04:48,434 --> 00:04:51,186
See? You can't give this stupid place up.

70
00:04:51,645 --> 00:04:54,189
How can you even talk about revenge?

71
00:04:54,273 --> 00:04:57,109
- Unbelievable.
- So we team up with Jeong Ho-myeong?

72
00:04:57,192 --> 00:05:00,529
And why shouldn't we?
We've been chasing Yoo and Han forever.

73
00:05:00,613 --> 00:05:03,073
We can't waste our whole lives here.

74
00:05:03,157 --> 00:05:05,701
I'd rather take action,
even if it's with Jeong Ho-myeong.

75
00:05:05,784 --> 00:05:09,496
Don't just keep saying no.
Try to be a little more open-minded.

76
00:05:10,205 --> 00:05:12,917
Just the other day,
you went after Yoo In-gu by yourself.

77
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:14,710
- What happened then?
- What did you say?

78
00:05:14,793 --> 00:05:16,545
You're getting old.

79
00:05:18,213 --> 00:05:19,506
You can't do anything by yourself anymore.

80
00:05:19,590 --> 00:05:21,091
So you're saying I'm washed up now?

81
00:05:21,175 --> 00:05:22,927
That's not what I'm talking about!

82
00:05:23,510 --> 00:05:25,262
Just get out of here, okay?

83
00:05:25,346 --> 00:05:27,389
Go on,
run to your precious Jeong Ho-myeong!

84
00:05:56,085 --> 00:05:59,588
You're getting old.
You can't do anything by yourself anymore.

85
00:06:25,781 --> 00:06:26,824
Watch your back!

86
00:07:00,357 --> 00:07:01,817
- Here.
- Yes.

87
00:07:11,618 --> 00:07:13,203
- Hey, Chow Yunfat.
- Yes.

88
00:07:13,829 --> 00:07:16,206
The entire Bamnabi Sect
has seen your face.

89
00:07:16,957 --> 00:07:18,625
It'll be tough to work as a waiter.

90
00:07:19,126 --> 00:07:21,170
- Do you have somewhere to go?
- Well...

91
00:07:22,504 --> 00:07:26,717
Well, if it's okay with you,
I'd like to work for you.

92
00:07:29,303 --> 00:07:30,512
Work for me?

93
00:07:31,346 --> 00:07:34,308
- Why?
- Well, I...

94
00:07:36,185 --> 00:07:37,644
I want to be like you.

95
00:07:51,658 --> 00:07:53,035
1,000,000 WON

96
00:07:55,496 --> 00:07:56,789
10,000 WON

97
00:07:59,708 --> 00:08:03,253
I appreciate your help today.
But this is where we part ways.

98
00:08:03,712 --> 00:08:04,838
Take this money.

99
00:08:05,339 --> 00:08:08,509
- Be on your way.
- Where would I even go?

100
00:08:08,592 --> 00:08:09,843
You want to be like me?

101
00:08:10,552 --> 00:08:12,054
And for what?

102
00:08:12,137 --> 00:08:14,139
You'd be a thug
who only knows how to fight.

103
00:08:14,932 --> 00:08:17,726
Don't get any crazy ideas. Start fresh.

104
00:08:28,153 --> 00:08:29,780
Chow

105
00:08:30,656 --> 00:08:32,116
After Chow Yun Fat...

106
00:08:32,616 --> 00:08:36,328
You're the first man
I've ever wanted to be like!

107
00:08:36,411 --> 00:08:38,455
It's not that I have some kind of fantasy.

108
00:08:38,539 --> 00:08:43,001
No matter where you go,
I want to follow you!

109
00:08:43,752 --> 00:08:46,088
And I want to be more like you!

110
00:08:47,005 --> 00:08:49,091
Please, take me in!

111
00:09:23,876 --> 00:09:25,586
Prosecutor Gang, you're coming with us.

112
00:09:39,683 --> 00:09:40,976
Those bastards.

113
00:09:42,394 --> 00:09:44,396
Okay, fine.

114
00:09:45,647 --> 00:09:47,858
So you want to take this all the way, huh?

115
00:09:49,193 --> 00:09:51,195
Yes, come in.

116
00:09:52,196 --> 00:09:55,115
So, our members would like to see you.

117
00:09:55,949 --> 00:09:58,368
- Members?
- The people from the shelter.

118
00:10:00,120 --> 00:10:02,956
I know it's late,
but thank you for saving me.

119
00:10:03,498 --> 00:10:05,918
Look, I don't need your gratitude.

120
00:10:06,001 --> 00:10:07,252
But I have a question.

121
00:10:08,587 --> 00:10:10,255
Why were you in the sea water?

122
00:10:10,839 --> 00:10:12,758
- Are you really a prosecutor?
- Hey!

123
00:10:13,342 --> 00:10:15,219
- I'm sorry.
- What? I'm curious.

124
00:10:15,302 --> 00:10:19,097
She had a prosecutor's ID,
but told us not to report anything.

125
00:10:19,181 --> 00:10:22,184
Is this going to be on the news?
We deserve to know.

126
00:10:26,104 --> 00:10:28,440
I was investigating a violent crime.

127
00:10:28,941 --> 00:10:31,401
I had an accident
during the investigation.

128
00:10:32,361 --> 00:10:34,738
And if my location is exposed,
it could be bad.

129
00:10:34,821 --> 00:10:37,199
It could seriously jeopardize
the whole investigation.

130
00:10:37,282 --> 00:10:39,409
I know this is a huge favor to ask.

131
00:10:39,534 --> 00:10:44,289
But could I stay here in secret
just for a short while?

132
00:10:44,373 --> 00:10:46,416
Oh, of course.

133
00:10:46,500 --> 00:10:49,169
So it's like a stakeout.
A sting operation.

134
00:10:49,253 --> 00:10:50,837
That's what it is.

135
00:10:51,338 --> 00:10:52,714
I'm a cop, so I get it.

136
00:10:53,924 --> 00:10:56,176
But are you sure you'll be okay here?

137
00:10:56,260 --> 00:11:00,931
Oh, yes, of course.
Mr. Bong told me what you all do here.

138
00:11:01,014 --> 00:11:04,977
You help victims who lost their property
by Heaven Capital.

139
00:11:05,060 --> 00:11:06,853
You take in people
with nowhere else to go.

140
00:11:06,937 --> 00:11:10,023
You're such wonderful people.
Of course I can trust you.

141
00:11:10,107 --> 00:11:11,191
Oh, please.

142
00:11:11,275 --> 00:11:14,820
We helped out some neighbors.
It's really nothing great.

143
00:11:14,903 --> 00:11:16,947
So, speaking of.

144
00:11:17,531 --> 00:11:20,701
I heard you've collected some materials
related to Heaven Capital here.

145
00:11:20,784 --> 00:11:24,162
May I look through them?

146
00:11:24,246 --> 00:11:26,415
I mean, that bastard Yoo In-gu...

147
00:11:26,498 --> 00:11:29,501
No, that's not what I mean.
This is about Heaven Capital.

148
00:11:29,626 --> 00:11:32,462
I'd like to see what illegal activities
they've been up to.

149
00:11:32,546 --> 00:11:34,673
I believe I can research things like that.

150
00:11:34,756 --> 00:11:37,426
You just woke up.
Aren't you pushing yourself?

151
00:11:37,509 --> 00:11:39,970
What's there to worry about?
You're here for her.

152
00:11:40,053 --> 00:11:41,680
- Excuse me?
- Just stick with her.

153
00:11:41,763 --> 00:11:44,349
Make sure she doesn't
have to lift a finger.

154
00:11:44,433 --> 00:11:45,475
But I'm tired.

155
00:11:45,559 --> 00:11:46,560
No, it's okay.

156
00:11:46,643 --> 00:11:49,271
I'd just like to look over the materials.

157
00:11:49,354 --> 00:11:51,315
No, no. You still have
trouble getting around.

158
00:11:51,398 --> 00:11:53,817
Je-sun can help you out a little longer.

159
00:11:53,900 --> 00:11:54,985
Yeah.

160
00:11:56,820 --> 00:11:58,655
I pulled an all-nighter yesterday.

161
00:12:14,171 --> 00:12:16,423
TEMPORARILY CLOSED. WE'LL BE BACK SOON.

162
00:12:18,550 --> 00:12:19,551
Hey.

163
00:12:31,521 --> 00:12:32,689
Can you handle it?

164
00:12:33,690 --> 00:12:34,691
Sir?

165
00:12:35,233 --> 00:12:36,985
Rebuilding Hwasan after a decade.

166
00:12:38,070 --> 00:12:41,031
Are you confident you can take down
the Ingu Sect and Han Gyeong-wook?

167
00:12:45,285 --> 00:12:46,286
Boss.

168
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:49,664
I've gotten rusty
after taking ten years off.

169
00:12:51,083 --> 00:12:54,294
So if you're going to whine
about me getting old...

170
00:12:54,378 --> 00:12:56,046
I'll just leave you here right now.

171
00:13:05,389 --> 00:13:06,890
I'd never do that!

172
00:13:06,973 --> 00:13:10,060
I've waited ten years for this day.

173
00:13:10,143 --> 00:13:11,311
I will do my best.

174
00:13:11,853 --> 00:13:15,357
Tell me everything that happened with
Yoo In-gu and Jeong Ho-myeong.

175
00:13:16,066 --> 00:13:17,484
And don't hide anything from me.

176
00:13:18,235 --> 00:13:19,736
And whatever we do,
we see it through together.

177
00:13:20,612 --> 00:13:23,824
- Yes, boss.
- And...

178
00:13:23,907 --> 00:13:26,910
Gong-bok, you were right.
I really have gotten old.

179
00:13:29,496 --> 00:13:32,332
- I don't think that's what I meant.
- No, it's true.

180
00:13:33,041 --> 00:13:36,002
I'm no match for the Ingu Sect on my own.

181
00:13:37,629 --> 00:13:39,297
Contact Jeong Ho-myeong and talk to him.

182
00:13:39,881 --> 00:13:42,259
- Tell him I want to see him now.
- Yes, sir.

183
00:13:48,014 --> 00:13:50,267
Hey, Mr. Yoo.

184
00:13:50,350 --> 00:13:52,644
Oh? You look happy. You're looking good.

185
00:13:53,186 --> 00:13:56,857
- So? Did everything work out?
- I took care of everything.

186
00:13:57,315 --> 00:14:00,318
Wow, for real? So fast, Mr. Yoo.

187
00:14:00,777 --> 00:14:04,030
So, what's your method?
You have to tell me your secret.

188
00:14:04,865 --> 00:14:07,784
It's something you could never pull off.
Don't get cute.

189
00:14:08,410 --> 00:14:10,704
Watch your mouth in front of Chief Han.
Got it?

190
00:14:11,621 --> 00:14:15,792
- Okay, got it.
- Here are the Imcheon mayoral polls.

191
00:14:15,876 --> 00:14:17,878
Between Kim Seon-jung
and Han Gyeong-wook...

192
00:14:17,961 --> 00:14:20,881
- I'm here.
- A two-way race has emerged.

193
00:14:20,964 --> 00:14:21,965
What are you doing?

194
00:14:22,048 --> 00:14:24,885
- A two-point gap.
- I see you're watching TV.

195
00:14:24,968 --> 00:14:28,597
Candidate Kim Seon-jung's strength
lies in his deep roots in Imcheon.

196
00:14:28,680 --> 00:14:31,683
He has established an image
as an incorruptible educator.

197
00:14:31,766 --> 00:14:36,313
He has become a rival to Han Gyeong-wook
in Imcheon's conservative stronghold.

198
00:14:36,438 --> 00:14:38,607
His approval ratings
have recently been soaring...

199
00:14:42,402 --> 00:14:44,988
You're keeping a close eye on the news.

200
00:14:45,864 --> 00:14:48,658
What's the point of watching the news?
It's all a bunch of nonsense.

201
00:14:49,618 --> 00:14:50,619
A bunch of nonsense?

202
00:14:50,702 --> 00:14:54,039
They can run their mouths all day,
but for our Yeongseon Island Project...

203
00:14:54,831 --> 00:14:58,043
You would have to
win this election, right?

204
00:14:58,960 --> 00:15:00,378
Chairman Do, your thoughts?

205
00:15:00,462 --> 00:15:04,090
Well, I have no doubt you will win.

206
00:15:04,174 --> 00:15:05,467
But that kind of bad news...

207
00:15:06,760 --> 00:15:08,428
Oh, I'm sorry. I just think...

208
00:15:08,512 --> 00:15:11,973
It's best to nip
these negative stories in the bud.

209
00:15:14,142 --> 00:15:17,187
Now you're talking, Mr. Do.

210
00:15:17,270 --> 00:15:19,231
Nipping things in the bud
is my specialty, isn't it?

211
00:15:19,314 --> 00:15:21,942
Kidnapping, blackmail...
Just say the word.

212
00:15:22,025 --> 00:15:23,235
Mr. Yoo.

213
00:15:24,236 --> 00:15:26,738
Can't you see I'm talking
to Mr. Do right now?

214
00:15:27,489 --> 00:15:29,741
Why do you keep spouting nonsense?

215
00:15:30,283 --> 00:15:31,576
I'm sorry.

216
00:15:32,619 --> 00:15:33,787
Go on, Mr. Do.

217
00:15:33,870 --> 00:15:37,624
Yes, an election is ultimately
a battle of images, isn't it?

218
00:15:38,416 --> 00:15:40,585
He's cultivated one
as an incorruptible educator.

219
00:15:40,669 --> 00:15:43,505
- So let's turn him into corrupt trash.
- How long will it take?

220
00:15:43,588 --> 00:15:46,007
A week? A week will be more than enough.

221
00:15:49,094 --> 00:15:50,178
Mr. Yoo.

222
00:15:51,012 --> 00:15:54,266
You'll support him.
Make sure it moves quickly.

223
00:15:54,391 --> 00:15:57,519
You want me to wipe his ass?

224
00:15:57,602 --> 00:15:58,979
I'm a busy man.

225
00:16:01,106 --> 00:16:05,944
I thought your company ran itself,
but you're busy?

226
00:16:06,778 --> 00:16:09,739
What? You got a side hustle
I don't know about?

227
00:16:11,700 --> 00:16:14,578
No, sir. I spoke out of turn.

228
00:16:16,121 --> 00:16:18,331
And just so we're clear.

229
00:16:19,165 --> 00:16:21,793
If anything goes wrong with this project

230
00:16:22,961 --> 00:16:25,505
all of you will be held responsible.

231
00:16:27,340 --> 00:16:30,176
- Do I make myself clear?
- Yes, sir. Understood.

232
00:16:49,571 --> 00:16:52,115
There's so much to do.
This is a real headache.

233
00:16:55,785 --> 00:16:56,911
Oh, Mr. Nam.

234
00:16:56,995 --> 00:16:58,705
Did you get
all the files from Secretary Baek?

235
00:16:58,788 --> 00:17:02,459
Yes. I received the files
on Kim Seon-jung.

236
00:17:02,542 --> 00:17:04,502
Give those files to Geum Kang-sik.

237
00:17:06,004 --> 00:17:09,257
Hey, Mr. Yoo, don't worry about this.
We'll take care of it.

238
00:17:09,341 --> 00:17:11,176
Hey, you think I want to work with you?

239
00:17:11,301 --> 00:17:12,802
With me?

240
00:17:13,803 --> 00:17:15,889
Weren't you told to support me?

241
00:17:16,348 --> 00:17:20,060
It's just that
I don't really need your support.

242
00:17:21,227 --> 00:17:24,189
This job doesn't call for
your brutish methods.

243
00:17:24,898 --> 00:17:27,525
What? Brutish? You son of a bitch.

244
00:17:30,445 --> 00:17:31,529
- Hey, Kang-sik.
- Yes, sir.

245
00:17:31,613 --> 00:17:34,199
Tomorrow, take the guys
and look into Kim Seon-jung.

246
00:17:34,324 --> 00:17:37,285
Sir? But Chairman Do just said
there was no need...

247
00:17:41,665 --> 00:17:42,957
Did you just dodge?

248
00:17:43,708 --> 00:17:46,211
Hey, did you take money
from that bastard or something?

249
00:17:47,045 --> 00:17:48,755
Do his words come before mine?

250
00:17:48,838 --> 00:17:49,839
No, sir.

251
00:17:50,674 --> 00:17:54,094
Kidnapping, blackmail, false imprisonment.

252
00:17:54,636 --> 00:17:58,056
Find anything on Kim Seon-jung
we can use as leverage.

253
00:17:58,139 --> 00:17:59,516
Don't come back empty-handed.

254
00:18:00,016 --> 00:18:01,976
- Got it?
- Yes, sir.

255
00:18:08,525 --> 00:18:09,818
Here's my decision.

256
00:18:10,985 --> 00:18:13,655
I'll accept your offer. On one condition.

257
00:18:13,738 --> 00:18:15,615
Don't even think about giving me orders.

258
00:18:16,366 --> 00:18:19,494
We're working together for a short time
to get what we both want.

259
00:18:20,161 --> 00:18:21,788
I have no intention of becoming your pawn.

260
00:18:24,499 --> 00:18:26,960
So you're determined
to hold on to your pride.

261
00:18:30,922 --> 00:18:32,507
Look here, you thug.

262
00:18:32,590 --> 00:18:36,094
What happens if you go rogue
and ruin the whole operation?

263
00:18:37,595 --> 00:18:40,473
- You want a piece of this thug?
- Boss, calm down. Please.

264
00:18:41,057 --> 00:18:44,394
Does he have a solid plan to take down
Yoo In-gu and Han Gyeong-wook?

265
00:18:44,477 --> 00:18:46,312
Or is he just trying to use us?

266
00:18:46,438 --> 00:18:51,192
Do you know what Yoo In-gu's doing,
or what Han Gyeong-wook is up to?

267
00:18:51,276 --> 00:18:54,738
- You don't have a clue, do you?
- Well...

268
00:18:54,821 --> 00:18:57,282
Ten years of scanning barcodes
has dulled your edge.

269
00:18:57,365 --> 00:19:00,034
Just follow my orders,
not question everything.

270
00:19:00,118 --> 00:19:02,620
Well, you spent ten years
working in a Chinese kitchen.

271
00:19:03,163 --> 00:19:06,082
Special agent, my ass.
When did you last wear a suit?

272
00:19:06,166 --> 00:19:07,667
Who's calling who washed up?

273
00:19:07,751 --> 00:19:09,544
You want to be the boss?
Let's settle this!

274
00:19:11,087 --> 00:19:12,839
Once a thug, always a thug.

275
00:19:12,922 --> 00:19:14,758
Think I can't take you? Huh?

276
00:19:14,841 --> 00:19:16,426
Don't you remember ten years ago?

277
00:19:16,509 --> 00:19:19,637
- Come on, this isn't why we met.
- Get out of my way!

278
00:19:19,721 --> 00:19:21,055
No, get out of the way.

279
00:19:21,139 --> 00:19:22,640
Of course I remember ten years ago.

280
00:19:22,724 --> 00:19:24,392
If it hadn't rained that day

281
00:19:24,476 --> 00:19:27,103
- I would've finished you for good!
- Wow, really?

282
00:19:27,187 --> 00:19:30,064
You're even dumber than you look.
Want me to give you a reminder?

283
00:19:30,148 --> 00:19:31,649
- Move!
- Get out of my way!

284
00:19:31,733 --> 00:19:32,776
- Go on, you bastard!
- Boss!

285
00:19:32,859 --> 00:19:34,277
- I said get out of my way!
- Boss!

286
00:19:34,360 --> 00:19:36,529
- Move, you punk!
- Bring it!

287
00:19:36,613 --> 00:19:39,282
- I'll teach him a lesson!
- Mr. Jeong!

288
00:19:39,365 --> 00:19:41,242
- Boss!
- Move!

289
00:19:41,326 --> 00:19:42,494
You're getting a call. Answer it!

290
00:19:42,577 --> 00:19:44,579
Get out of my way!

291
00:19:44,662 --> 00:19:47,373
- I'll teach him a lesson.
- Answer your phone!

292
00:19:48,500 --> 00:19:49,667
You're getting a call!

293
00:19:57,050 --> 00:19:58,051
JO SEONG-WON

294
00:19:58,885 --> 00:20:01,221
- Yeah?
- Hey, Prosecutor Gang's alive.

295
00:20:01,763 --> 00:20:04,265
- Really?
- I don't know where she went yet.

296
00:20:04,349 --> 00:20:05,767
But I think she washed ashore.

297
00:20:05,850 --> 00:20:08,144
How's your end?
Any progress with Gang Beom-ryong?

298
00:20:09,270 --> 00:20:12,065
- What are you looking at?
- I'm working on it. I'll call you back.

299
00:20:13,525 --> 00:20:15,735
- Move!
- Come on!

300
00:20:27,413 --> 00:20:28,706
Gang is alive.

301
00:20:28,790 --> 00:20:30,708
- For real?
- Of course. Damn it.

302
00:20:30,792 --> 00:20:33,670
Boss, that means
we don't have to do this, right?

303
00:20:34,838 --> 00:20:38,049
Mr. Jeong, do you want to
waste your energy fighting him?

304
00:20:39,968 --> 00:20:43,263
All right, fine. Have it your way.
A temporary alliance it is.

305
00:20:43,847 --> 00:20:45,640
We know Gang is alive now.

306
00:20:45,723 --> 00:20:48,101
- We can't waste time.
- Then let's be clear.

307
00:20:48,935 --> 00:20:49,936
We don't work for you.

308
00:20:50,019 --> 00:20:53,022
Jeez, I get it.
Call it whatever you want, I don't care.

309
00:20:53,106 --> 00:20:55,358
But don't question my operation again.

310
00:20:55,984 --> 00:20:59,320
- Or this alliance is over. Got it?
- Fine!

311
00:21:02,615 --> 00:21:04,576
JEONGSEOK SINGLE ROOMS

312
00:21:06,911 --> 00:21:11,708
Most of the victims were people
who gambled at Heaven Casino.

313
00:21:11,791 --> 00:21:15,461
They lured in ordinary residents
and got them into gambling debt.

314
00:21:15,545 --> 00:21:18,172
And then they intentionally confiscated
their homes and land.

315
00:21:18,256 --> 00:21:19,549
But it's strange.

316
00:21:25,513 --> 00:21:29,142
On Yeongseon Island, they only took land
from Nakwon-ri residents.

317
00:21:29,225 --> 00:21:30,226
NAKWON-RI

318
00:21:30,310 --> 00:21:31,352
But why?

319
00:21:32,061 --> 00:21:35,982
Properties in a small village
are a hassle to sell.

320
00:21:36,065 --> 00:21:38,943
Even with development plans,
it'd take a long time to profit.

321
00:21:40,570 --> 00:21:44,032
Yoo In-gu is definitely acting
on Han Gyeong-wook's orders.

322
00:21:44,490 --> 00:21:47,035
So why would Han Gyeong-wook
give such an order?

323
00:21:48,369 --> 00:21:52,832
- They're using Yeongseon Island to...
- Here's your meal.

324
00:21:52,916 --> 00:21:53,917
Oh, thanks.

325
00:21:57,879 --> 00:21:59,172
Come in.

326
00:22:00,715 --> 00:22:02,008
Here you go.

327
00:22:02,091 --> 00:22:04,427
Oh, thank you. Just leave it there.
I'll eat in a bit.

328
00:22:04,510 --> 00:22:06,137
Oh, okay.

329
00:22:06,220 --> 00:22:08,973
Hey, can I ask you something?

330
00:22:10,725 --> 00:22:13,895
Do you think there's a way
for the victims to get their homes back?

331
00:22:13,978 --> 00:22:16,147
Well, I'm not sure yet.

332
00:22:18,066 --> 00:22:19,275
You should eat something first.

333
00:22:19,359 --> 00:22:21,694
Yes, if you just leave it,
I'll eat it. Thank you.

334
00:22:21,819 --> 00:22:24,364
You have to eat before it gets cold.
And take your medicine.

335
00:22:24,447 --> 00:22:27,158
Just a moment. There we go.

336
00:22:35,917 --> 00:22:37,710
Say ah.

337
00:22:39,796 --> 00:22:41,673
- Can I do it myself?
- Of course.

338
00:22:41,756 --> 00:22:43,800
Thank you.

339
00:22:43,925 --> 00:22:46,844
After you finish the porridge,
make sure you take your meds.

340
00:22:48,388 --> 00:22:52,141
If you get seawater in your ear,
you can get a nasty ear infection.

341
00:22:55,603 --> 00:22:58,272
- Are you a nurse, by any chance?
- Huh?

342
00:22:58,356 --> 00:23:00,608
It's just,
you seem to be a natural at this.

343
00:23:01,609 --> 00:23:04,529
I fell into the ocean ten years ago,
just like you.

344
00:23:04,654 --> 00:23:08,199
I'm just doing for you
what the person who saved me did.

345
00:23:08,282 --> 00:23:10,785
- Why did you fall in?
- I have no idea.

346
00:23:10,868 --> 00:23:12,120
What?

347
00:23:12,203 --> 00:23:15,206
Oh, there's no water.
I'll get you some warm water.

348
00:23:15,289 --> 00:23:17,417
Eat up before it gets cold.

349
00:23:18,084 --> 00:23:19,961
So busy today.

350
00:23:23,256 --> 00:23:27,468
Ah, to meet the two men
who once ruled the Hwasan Sect.

351
00:23:27,552 --> 00:23:30,555
- It's an honor to meet you.
- The honor is all mine.

352
00:23:30,638 --> 00:23:32,849
Why are you being so formal
with these thugs?

353
00:23:34,183 --> 00:23:37,395
We may not have started off
on the right foot.

354
00:23:37,478 --> 00:23:39,230
But let's put the past behind us...

355
00:23:39,313 --> 00:23:42,442
- and focus on what's ahead.
- Yes, I'll do my absolute best.

356
00:23:43,234 --> 00:23:46,070
But is Prosecutor Gang really alive?

357
00:23:46,195 --> 00:23:48,364
Yes, we're certain she's alive.

358
00:23:48,448 --> 00:23:50,700
It'll take some time
to pinpoint her location.

359
00:23:51,325 --> 00:23:54,537
But before that,
there's something I need you two to do.

360
00:23:54,620 --> 00:23:57,582
Not Ma Gong-bok.
I need him to keep tabs on Bulgae.

361
00:23:58,458 --> 00:24:01,753
Hey, so about Bulgae.

362
00:24:02,295 --> 00:24:04,630
He was chased by the Heaven Capital guys
and got away.

363
00:24:04,714 --> 00:24:06,966
- So you lost him?
- We're looking. We'll find him.

364
00:24:07,050 --> 00:24:08,551
Are you kidding me?

365
00:24:09,886 --> 00:24:10,928
Hey.

366
00:24:11,012 --> 00:24:12,972
It's not like you weren't distracted
with other things yourself.

367
00:24:13,056 --> 00:24:14,474
You two are a real piece of work.

368
00:24:14,557 --> 00:24:15,808
Relax.

369
00:24:15,892 --> 00:24:18,186
There's something more urgent
than finding this Bulgae.

370
00:24:19,437 --> 00:24:22,565
Remember what Yoo In-gu said
when we bugged him?

371
00:24:23,733 --> 00:24:24,734
- The drug deal.
- What?

372
00:24:24,817 --> 00:24:25,818
- What?
- What?

373
00:24:25,902 --> 00:24:27,695
That bastard Yoo In-gu is dealing drugs?

374
00:24:27,779 --> 00:24:30,031
He said soon,
they'd be making a huge deal.

375
00:24:30,114 --> 00:24:34,160
One that will decide their fate.
The question is, how do we stop them?

376
00:24:34,243 --> 00:24:37,580
Wait a minute.
Can the four of us stop that?

377
00:24:37,663 --> 00:24:38,998
I mean, I hate to admit it.

378
00:24:39,082 --> 00:24:43,461
But the Ingu Sect is way too big
for just the four of us to take on.

379
00:24:43,544 --> 00:24:46,631
Since we're doing this anyway,
let's just go straight for the top.

380
00:24:46,714 --> 00:24:50,051
Do you think Yoo In-gu or Han Gyeong-wook
will even bat an eye over one deal?

381
00:24:50,134 --> 00:24:52,887
Typical thug mindset.
You only see what's in front of you.

382
00:24:52,970 --> 00:24:54,847
- What?
- You take out the boss, then what?

383
00:24:54,931 --> 00:24:56,766
You just bury him?

384
00:24:56,849 --> 00:24:57,850
And Gang Beom-ryong,

385
00:24:57,934 --> 00:25:00,478
did you forget what happened
when you charged in alone?

386
00:25:01,646 --> 00:25:05,066
Those bastards have built a fortress.

387
00:25:05,149 --> 00:25:06,526
You want to tear it down?

388
00:25:06,609 --> 00:25:09,028
You have to take it down step by step.

389
00:25:09,862 --> 00:25:13,866
Our priority is to stop the drug deal
and land a critical blow.

390
00:25:13,991 --> 00:25:16,285
So you have a plan?

391
00:25:19,330 --> 00:25:20,623
First, Ma Gong-bok.

392
00:25:21,791 --> 00:25:25,795
Put your search for Bulgae on hold,
and start looking into Yoo In-gu.

393
00:25:26,504 --> 00:25:28,798
Don't miss a single thing they do.

394
00:25:29,632 --> 00:25:32,009
- Yes, sir.
- Hey, Ho-myeong.

395
00:25:32,093 --> 00:25:34,512
Tailing, wiretapping...
This isn't child's play.

396
00:25:34,595 --> 00:25:35,972
You sure a civilian can handle it?

397
00:25:36,055 --> 00:25:37,348
He's not just a civilian.

398
00:25:37,431 --> 00:25:41,519
He stalked me, an elite agent,
for ten whole years.

399
00:25:43,020 --> 00:25:44,730
Well, I don't mean to brag.

400
00:25:44,814 --> 00:25:47,650
But I know his anniversary,
Ji-woo's birthday

401
00:25:47,733 --> 00:25:49,527
and how many spoons he owns.

402
00:25:49,610 --> 00:25:53,364
Just let me know if you ever need to
tail someone and gather intel.

403
00:25:54,240 --> 00:25:55,241
Nice.

404
00:25:55,324 --> 00:25:58,119
See? Now you get
how creepy and relentless he is.

405
00:26:00,204 --> 00:26:03,666
And you, with your leg,
don't even think about overdoing it.

406
00:26:03,749 --> 00:26:06,836
Go through the police CCTV footage
he has access to.

407
00:26:06,919 --> 00:26:09,797
- Track Prosecutor Gang.
- Okay, got it.

408
00:26:14,177 --> 00:26:17,180
What? What do you want from me?

409
00:26:18,181 --> 00:26:20,683
- You just get ready.
- I'm already ready. Ready for what?

410
00:26:20,766 --> 00:26:21,809
To run like a dog.

411
00:26:30,109 --> 00:26:31,277
Try not to wreck the car.

412
00:26:31,360 --> 00:26:34,197
I haven't forgotten
about that scratch on the door.

413
00:26:34,280 --> 00:26:36,240
Jeez, I know. I'll be careful.

414
00:26:39,118 --> 00:26:40,494
Thank you.

415
00:26:40,578 --> 00:26:43,164
I saw the dent in the back too!

416
00:26:43,247 --> 00:26:47,335
I told you that wasn't me.
For goodness' sake.

417
00:26:52,882 --> 00:26:55,259
I'll be on my way. See you in the evening.

418
00:26:55,384 --> 00:26:57,136
- Say hi to Seon-jung for me.
- Okay.

419
00:27:34,257 --> 00:27:35,967
- Oh, dear.
- Oh, hey.

420
00:27:36,050 --> 00:27:37,760
- Welcome.
- Hey, O-ran!

421
00:27:39,887 --> 00:27:40,930
- Boss.
- Yeah.

422
00:27:41,013 --> 00:27:42,974
A woman just went into
Kim Seon-jung's house.

423
00:27:43,891 --> 00:27:45,059
Get a picture.

424
00:27:47,645 --> 00:27:48,729
Did you get it?

425
00:27:52,149 --> 00:27:54,610
But boss, seriously,
isn't this a bit much?

426
00:27:54,735 --> 00:27:56,988
We're already swamped with the drug deal.

427
00:27:57,071 --> 00:28:00,408
Plus the Martial Arts Master,
and now Kim Seon-jung, too?

428
00:28:01,075 --> 00:28:03,703
The guys are complaining,
saying it's too much work.

429
00:28:03,828 --> 00:28:06,330
If you don't use your brain,
your body pays the price.

430
00:28:07,957 --> 00:28:11,794
If you and I want to save our own skin,
we better do whatever we can.

431
00:28:12,169 --> 00:28:14,922
We must get new intel
on Kim Seon-jung before Jo does.

432
00:28:16,549 --> 00:28:19,093
- But for how long?
- Suck it up a little longer, you punk!

433
00:28:22,513 --> 00:28:25,224
This will all be over soon.

434
00:28:28,144 --> 00:28:30,438
All right. Look here.

435
00:28:33,524 --> 00:28:35,067
- See? This is rice...
- Yes.

436
00:28:35,735 --> 00:28:38,988
Underneath are beans, barley, potatoes,
and sweet potatoes.

437
00:28:39,071 --> 00:28:41,407
I was going to donate this
to a homeless shelter.

438
00:28:42,199 --> 00:28:44,660
But you all need it more right now,
so take it.

439
00:28:45,286 --> 00:28:46,912
I'm so sorry.

440
00:28:46,996 --> 00:28:49,999
- I'm sorry for always whining.
- How are the victims?

441
00:28:50,082 --> 00:28:53,169
- Is the number still increasing?
- Yes.

442
00:28:54,086 --> 00:28:58,215
We're gathering all the evidence,
but Heaven Capital must've pulled strings.

443
00:28:58,299 --> 00:29:01,218
Police and lawyers keep saying
nothing illegal occurred.

444
00:29:01,302 --> 00:29:04,889
Even reporters don't care,
saying it's not newsworthy.

445
00:29:05,598 --> 00:29:09,810
- I don't know what I should do now.
- Damn it. Just hold on a little longer.

446
00:29:09,894 --> 00:29:12,229
Wait until I get elected.

447
00:29:12,313 --> 00:29:15,274
The first thing I'll do is
create a relief plan for the victims.

448
00:29:15,358 --> 00:29:19,487
- How ambitious.
- I'm number one in the polls, kid.

449
00:29:19,570 --> 00:29:20,988
I know.

450
00:29:21,072 --> 00:29:24,116
That's why you need to get elected soon.

451
00:29:24,784 --> 00:29:27,370
At this rate, everyone on
Yeongseon Island will be ruined.

452
00:29:27,453 --> 00:29:29,663
Let's just hang in there
a little longer, huh?

453
00:29:29,747 --> 00:29:31,332
Okay.

454
00:29:31,415 --> 00:29:33,542
- Hand me that one.
- Here.

455
00:29:36,420 --> 00:29:40,049
- We'll put this to good use, sir.
- Let me know if you need more.

456
00:29:40,132 --> 00:29:42,093
- Thank you.
- You should get going.

457
00:29:42,843 --> 00:29:44,387
- I'll see you later.
- Okay then.

458
00:29:49,100 --> 00:29:50,101
Huh?

459
00:29:50,768 --> 00:29:51,769
She's driving away.

460
00:29:52,686 --> 00:29:54,897
- What do we do?
- Obviously, we follow her.

461
00:29:59,860 --> 00:30:02,279
Wait, who's that?
I feel like I've seen her before.

462
00:30:47,908 --> 00:30:48,951
Switch.

463
00:30:56,876 --> 00:30:59,253
Damn it. She's onto us.

464
00:30:59,336 --> 00:31:01,046
I told you to keep some distance.

465
00:31:24,320 --> 00:31:26,614
- Perfect. Now get right on her tail.
- Yes, sir.

466
00:31:56,185 --> 00:31:58,395
It's a dead end.

467
00:31:58,521 --> 00:31:59,772
- Right.
- Hey, get ready.

468
00:31:59,855 --> 00:32:01,524
- Right.
- Kill the engine.

469
00:33:15,139 --> 00:33:16,140
IMCHEON 30 BA 8690

470
00:33:18,642 --> 00:33:24,648
ORAN CHINESE RESTAURANT

471
00:33:27,443 --> 00:33:28,444
Cuckoo!

472
00:33:32,948 --> 00:33:33,949
Cuckoo!

473
00:33:34,033 --> 00:33:36,785
- Ji-woo.
- Daddy! It's Daddy!

474
00:33:36,869 --> 00:33:40,914
- Ji-woo. Hey there. Have you been well?
- Uh-huh.

475
00:33:40,998 --> 00:33:43,584
- Have you eaten today?
- Daddy, I missed you.

476
00:33:43,667 --> 00:33:46,170
I missed you too.

477
00:33:46,253 --> 00:33:48,297
What's with the dramatic family reunion?

478
00:33:50,924 --> 00:33:52,217
Hey, Jeong.

479
00:33:53,969 --> 00:33:56,805
Whoa, you scared me.
What brings you out so early?

480
00:33:56,889 --> 00:33:57,973
Where have you been?

481
00:33:58,641 --> 00:33:59,808
Do you know how worried we've been?

482
00:33:59,892 --> 00:34:01,226
Ever since you left

483
00:34:02,102 --> 00:34:04,772
the two of us have had it so rough,
you have no idea.

484
00:34:04,855 --> 00:34:08,817
O-ran is always out and about
with her K-pop obsession.

485
00:34:08,901 --> 00:34:13,906
At this rate,
we're going to work ourselves to death.

486
00:34:13,989 --> 00:34:15,324
You're back for good, right?

487
00:34:15,407 --> 00:34:16,700
You're not leaving again, are you?

488
00:34:18,118 --> 00:34:20,537
Daddy? Are you back for good?

489
00:34:22,081 --> 00:34:25,584
I just stopped by for a bit today
to see Ji-woo.

490
00:34:27,753 --> 00:34:30,589
When on earth are you going to
make up with O-ran, huh?

491
00:34:30,673 --> 00:34:33,300
She blocked my number,
so there's nothing I can do.

492
00:34:33,384 --> 00:34:36,303
- A letter. You could write her a letter.
- She'd just tear it up.

493
00:34:36,387 --> 00:34:39,723
So you're just going to do nothing?
You're not going to come back?

494
00:34:39,807 --> 00:34:43,644
To make up with Ji-woo's mom,
there's something I need to take care of.

495
00:34:43,727 --> 00:34:45,312
I'll come back after I've finished it.

496
00:34:46,438 --> 00:34:49,650
Daddy, when are you coming home?

497
00:34:52,986 --> 00:34:54,655
I'll be back as soon as I can.

498
00:34:57,199 --> 00:34:58,867
Hey. so...

499
00:34:58,951 --> 00:35:01,912
Since you're here,
can you peel some onions before you go?

500
00:35:03,080 --> 00:35:05,165
Do you have any incense left at home?

501
00:35:11,255 --> 00:35:18,262
STORE CLOSING
CLEARANCE SALE

502
00:35:20,889 --> 00:35:21,890
Boss.

503
00:35:22,683 --> 00:35:24,435
We got this new sour chicken lunch box.

504
00:35:24,518 --> 00:35:25,894
Can I try one?

505
00:35:25,978 --> 00:35:28,731
Go ahead.
There's no one else to eat it anyway.

506
00:35:30,607 --> 00:35:34,111
Were you saving it
for that police officer?

507
00:35:34,194 --> 00:35:37,573
- In that case, I won't have it.
- No, go ahead and eat.

508
00:35:38,490 --> 00:35:39,575
She won't be coming by anyway.

509
00:35:40,492 --> 00:35:42,870
Huh?
What do you mean, she won't be coming?

510
00:35:43,579 --> 00:35:44,872
Did you end things with her?

511
00:35:47,207 --> 00:35:50,294
There was nothing to end.
We were never anything to begin with.

512
00:35:52,588 --> 00:35:53,964
Just eat it so I don't have to see it.

513
00:35:54,047 --> 00:35:57,384
Yes, sir. I'll get it out of your sight.

514
00:36:06,226 --> 00:36:07,227
Mr. Gang!

515
00:36:09,396 --> 00:36:12,107
- You're early.
- I came as soon as you called.

516
00:36:12,191 --> 00:36:14,735
What's this about?
Why are you quitting all of a sudden?

517
00:36:14,818 --> 00:36:16,069
Let's talk inside.

518
00:36:16,153 --> 00:36:18,405
- Stay and eat.
- Yes, sir.

519
00:36:41,220 --> 00:36:42,221
Hold it.

520
00:36:46,767 --> 00:36:47,976
What is it?

521
00:36:48,519 --> 00:36:52,147
There's a store called 25 O'Clock
about 300 meters from here.

522
00:36:52,815 --> 00:36:54,942
- From now on, please go there instead.
- Excuse me?

523
00:37:01,114 --> 00:37:04,159
Is that what your boss said?
That I shouldn't come?

524
00:37:05,452 --> 00:37:07,371
I hate to say this, but...

525
00:37:07,496 --> 00:37:11,917
My boss lives
in a different world from you.

526
00:37:12,000 --> 00:37:15,420
He has big things ahead of him,
so don't be a distraction.

527
00:37:15,504 --> 00:37:19,967
- You should just back off now.
- Big things?

528
00:37:20,050 --> 00:37:21,260
What?

529
00:37:21,343 --> 00:37:23,095
Is he opening a supermarket or something?

530
00:37:23,846 --> 00:37:26,098
And what gives you the right
to say something like that?

531
00:37:27,891 --> 00:37:31,562
I know my boss better than anyone.

532
00:37:31,645 --> 00:37:33,313
Anyone in the world.

533
00:37:34,314 --> 00:37:38,235
Do you have any idea
how much of a nuisance you've been to him?

534
00:37:39,987 --> 00:37:41,113
Is that what he said?

535
00:37:43,156 --> 00:37:45,951
- That I was a nuisance?
- Yes, he said it himself.

536
00:37:46,577 --> 00:37:50,414
He said you were driving him crazy
when you're not even together.

537
00:37:52,666 --> 00:37:56,503
Another Friendly Convenience Store award,
and you'll get even more perks from HQ.

538
00:37:56,587 --> 00:37:59,756
- Please, think it over.
- It's just that something's come up.

539
00:37:59,840 --> 00:38:02,134
- Sorry this is so sudden.
- I don't know how to tell you this.

540
00:38:03,343 --> 00:38:04,761
But you can't close right away.

541
00:38:04,845 --> 00:38:08,140
- It'll take at least three months.
- Please do it as quickly as you can.

542
00:38:13,145 --> 00:38:14,146
Just a moment.

543
00:38:14,730 --> 00:38:16,106
I'll be taking inventory.

544
00:38:24,072 --> 00:38:27,242
- Did the headquarters...
- Jesus! Don't creep up on me!

545
00:38:27,326 --> 00:38:29,411
I've been right here the whole time.

546
00:38:30,412 --> 00:38:35,042
- No, but just now...
- Oh, the cop? She's crazy.

547
00:38:36,293 --> 00:38:38,045
- I sent her away.
- Crazy?

548
00:38:39,254 --> 00:38:40,255
You sent her away?

549
00:38:40,339 --> 00:38:42,883
Didn't you say you two were nothing?

550
00:38:42,966 --> 00:38:46,094
She keeps coming to the store,
so she's a distraction.

551
00:38:47,012 --> 00:38:49,556
So I just took care of her myself.

552
00:38:49,640 --> 00:38:51,433
What do you mean, you took care of her?

553
00:38:51,934 --> 00:38:55,270
Have you really not noticed
the way she looks at you?

554
00:38:55,812 --> 00:38:58,398
- She's into you.
- Really?

555
00:39:00,025 --> 00:39:02,819
- How would you know that?
- Hey, what do you mean, how?

556
00:39:03,946 --> 00:39:07,658
Do you have any idea how many girls
come here just to give me drinks?

557
00:39:08,617 --> 00:39:12,579
That officer had the exact same look
when she was looking at you.

558
00:39:14,498 --> 00:39:16,917
It's a good thing I nipped it in the bud.

559
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:19,836
What would've happened
if you two had hit it off? Huh?

560
00:39:20,337 --> 00:39:23,006
Next thing you know,
you would have ended up on TV.

561
00:39:23,090 --> 00:39:28,095
The headline would read
"Collusion Between Ex-Gangster and Cop."

562
00:39:28,845 --> 00:39:31,056
Just the thought of it gives me chills.

563
00:39:32,599 --> 00:39:33,767
I did good, right?

564
00:39:35,435 --> 00:39:37,771
You're right about everything.

565
00:39:37,854 --> 00:39:39,022
Let's go with that.

566
00:39:39,106 --> 00:39:43,860
That could've been a disaster.
I really saved the day.

567
00:39:43,944 --> 00:39:45,737
HANMAEUM K-POP

568
00:39:45,821 --> 00:39:47,739
The number you have dialed
is unavailable...

569
00:39:52,035 --> 00:39:53,495
I was too harsh.

570
00:39:54,496 --> 00:39:56,873
Just tell me where you are.

571
00:40:12,973 --> 00:40:15,434
The number you are trying to reach...

572
00:40:20,897 --> 00:40:23,025
UNCLE: I WAS TOO HARSH.
JUST TELL ME WHERE YOU ARE.

573
00:40:27,988 --> 00:40:29,740
Who is it? Your uncle?

574
00:40:31,199 --> 00:40:32,200
Yeah.

575
00:40:32,284 --> 00:40:34,578
Just swallow your pride, apologize,
and go home.

576
00:40:34,661 --> 00:40:37,956
Damn it, are you crazy? I've got my pride.

577
00:40:39,750 --> 00:40:41,376
How can I just go back now?

578
00:40:41,460 --> 00:40:43,086
You're out of money for the PC cafe.

579
00:40:43,170 --> 00:40:45,255
Go home and get some money at least.

580
00:40:46,214 --> 00:40:49,259
Do you really think
I'm that much of a scumbag?

581
00:40:49,342 --> 00:40:52,512
Hey, that man is practically
living like a slave because of me.

582
00:40:52,596 --> 00:40:53,847
You want me to take his money?

583
00:40:54,806 --> 00:40:57,142
When will you grow up?

584
00:40:59,728 --> 00:41:02,981
I'll go back when I can pay him back,
plus extra, and free him.

585
00:41:03,774 --> 00:41:05,942
That's when I'll go back. In style.

586
00:41:06,026 --> 00:41:07,486
You're broke.
You think you can pull that off?

587
00:41:08,111 --> 00:41:09,571
That's why I'm trying to earn money.

588
00:41:09,654 --> 00:41:11,990
I'm scouring the part-time job sites now.

589
00:41:13,116 --> 00:41:14,534
NIGHT SHIFT, SERVERS, ENGLISH TUTOR WANTED

590
00:41:15,327 --> 00:41:18,288
Man, why is the pay so crappy
for all of these?

591
00:41:18,789 --> 00:41:20,082
Ah, damn it.

592
00:41:22,250 --> 00:41:24,294
Hey, Nam-il, I saw Jin-su yesterday.

593
00:41:24,377 --> 00:41:26,546
He said there's a gig that pays well.

594
00:41:26,630 --> 00:41:28,340
But they can't find anyone for it.

595
00:41:28,423 --> 00:41:31,426
If you're interested,
should I ask him about it for you?

596
00:41:31,510 --> 00:41:33,428
- It's not a scam, is it?
- Can't be a proper job.

597
00:41:33,929 --> 00:41:35,347
It pays a million won a day.

598
00:41:35,430 --> 00:41:38,809
What? One million won? For real?

599
00:41:47,150 --> 00:41:48,485
HEAVEN CAPITAL VICTIMS RECORD

600
00:41:52,405 --> 00:41:53,824
BONG JE-SUN / HEO NAM-IL

601
00:41:56,243 --> 00:41:57,536
Bong Je-sun.

602
00:42:02,082 --> 00:42:03,375
Yes.

603
00:42:04,876 --> 00:42:06,294
Oh, dear.

604
00:42:06,378 --> 00:42:09,214
I've prepared a nourishing meal
for you today.

605
00:42:10,674 --> 00:42:13,093
Here you go. There.

606
00:42:13,927 --> 00:42:15,303
This isn't just any regular chicken.

607
00:42:15,804 --> 00:42:19,558
It's made with a free-range chicken.
Looks delicious, right?

608
00:42:21,977 --> 00:42:23,019
Wow.

609
00:42:28,108 --> 00:42:29,192
Je-sun.

610
00:42:29,651 --> 00:42:31,403
- Yes?
- Mind if I eat with my own hands?

611
00:42:31,486 --> 00:42:32,654
- Of course.
- Okay.

612
00:42:32,737 --> 00:42:33,738
Sorry.

613
00:42:38,952 --> 00:42:39,953
Thank you.

614
00:42:40,871 --> 00:42:43,081
I'll get the bones out for you.

615
00:42:43,165 --> 00:42:45,750
Je-sun, why are you always hanging around?
Don't you have a job?

616
00:42:48,170 --> 00:42:49,379
This is my job.

617
00:42:49,462 --> 00:42:52,090
- Huh?
- Well...

618
00:42:53,175 --> 00:42:55,510
i used to have an office job,
but I got fired.

619
00:42:56,595 --> 00:43:00,807
Those thugs from Heaven Capital
came to my workplace and caused a scene.

620
00:43:00,891 --> 00:43:04,352
I see your name, Bong Je-sun,
on the victim list here.

621
00:43:05,187 --> 00:43:08,023
- Did you gamble?
- Not me. My nephew did.

622
00:43:08,690 --> 00:43:10,859
It wasn't even a large amount.
He got scammed.

623
00:43:10,942 --> 00:43:13,904
He's not even your own son.
Who takes on their nephew's debt?

624
00:43:15,113 --> 00:43:16,281
Wait.

625
00:43:16,865 --> 00:43:19,242
- Did you cosign for him?
- No, not exactly.

626
00:43:20,493 --> 00:43:23,872
It's just...
I couldn't just turn my back on him.

627
00:43:24,331 --> 00:43:28,627
Remember when I told you
I fell in the sea ten years back?

628
00:43:28,710 --> 00:43:33,548
These people came and rescued me,
and I had no memory or a place to go.

629
00:43:33,673 --> 00:43:37,385
They took me in as their son and uncle.

630
00:43:38,887 --> 00:43:41,723
So that's why you said you don't know
how you ended up in the water.

631
00:43:42,682 --> 00:43:44,559
Incredible.
It's like something out of a movie.

632
00:43:45,268 --> 00:43:48,980
- So you don't remember anything?
- It's a funny thing, right?

633
00:43:50,398 --> 00:43:53,610
I even tried hypnotherapy,
but it was no use.

634
00:43:53,693 --> 00:43:57,656
It only had me dreaming something
like a scene out of an action movie.

635
00:43:57,739 --> 00:43:59,115
-An action movie?
-Yes.

636
00:43:59,199 --> 00:44:00,242
Come in.

637
00:44:02,077 --> 00:44:04,412
Hi, Prosecutor Gang.

638
00:44:04,537 --> 00:44:07,582
I've something I need to discuss with you.
Do you have a moment?

639
00:44:07,666 --> 00:44:08,917
With me?

640
00:44:09,709 --> 00:44:12,796
You said two men followed you
when you left Seon-jung's house yesterday?

641
00:44:13,380 --> 00:44:18,593
Yes. But I'm not entirely sure.

642
00:44:19,261 --> 00:44:21,721
I'm pretty sure they were tailing me,
you know?

643
00:44:21,805 --> 00:44:23,932
So I couldn't let them follow me here.

644
00:44:24,015 --> 00:44:26,101
So I hid in an alley.
It was either me or them.

645
00:44:26,184 --> 00:44:28,561
I grabbed a wooden plank
and waited for them.

646
00:44:30,188 --> 00:44:31,606
But they just suddenly vanished.

647
00:44:32,065 --> 00:44:35,235
From the glimpse I got,
they didn't seem like regular guys.

648
00:44:35,318 --> 00:44:38,697
They looked just like the thugs
that work for Heaven Capital.

649
00:44:39,322 --> 00:44:43,952
What if they found out
we're helping the collection victims?

650
00:44:44,035 --> 00:44:45,578
What if that's why they followed me?

651
00:44:46,162 --> 00:44:48,790
But why didn't you call the police
right on the spot?

652
00:44:48,873 --> 00:44:50,166
Well, you see...

653
00:44:50,250 --> 00:44:53,461
If they're from the loan company,
it's useless to report them.

654
00:44:53,545 --> 00:44:57,757
I mean, how do you think they get away
with locking people up and beating them?

655
00:44:57,841 --> 00:44:59,592
Who do you think is backing them?

656
00:45:00,051 --> 00:45:02,012
It's no use to call the cops.

657
00:45:02,095 --> 00:45:03,555
They'd have gotten off with a warning.

658
00:45:04,180 --> 00:45:06,391
- Is it that bad?
- You don't have to look far.

659
00:45:07,309 --> 00:45:11,396
My superior, Sergeant Kim,
is a stooge for those loan sharks.

660
00:45:12,230 --> 00:45:14,524
What do we do
if it's really the Heaven Capital guys?

661
00:45:14,607 --> 00:45:16,901
I think we need to come up with a plan.

662
00:45:16,985 --> 00:45:19,070
We face them head-on. How about it?

663
00:45:19,154 --> 00:45:21,531
- Face them head-on?
- Yes. Okay.

664
00:45:22,282 --> 00:45:25,076
Could you tell me more
about this Detective Kim?

665
00:45:27,203 --> 00:45:30,248
Code One. 34 Nakwon 2-ro.
Assault reported.

666
00:45:30,373 --> 00:45:34,294
Yeah, I'm nearby. I'll take it.

667
00:45:38,256 --> 00:45:39,674
DETECTIVE KIM: DISPATCH IN 3

668
00:45:40,133 --> 00:45:41,509
Hey, stop it.

669
00:45:41,593 --> 00:45:43,636
- Let's go.
- Yes, boss.

670
00:45:43,720 --> 00:45:45,722
Everyone on Yeongseon Island knows him.

671
00:45:47,098 --> 00:45:48,600
He's supposed to be a cop.

672
00:45:48,683 --> 00:45:52,687
But instead of stopping debt collectors,
he covers for them.

673
00:45:52,771 --> 00:45:57,150
- There must be cameras around there.
- There were none.

674
00:45:57,233 --> 00:45:58,735
Are the police allowed to do this?

675
00:45:58,818 --> 00:46:01,488
How can a regular citizen
get the CCTV footage?

676
00:46:05,408 --> 00:46:09,079
As if taking bribes wasn't bad enough,
he's been corrupting his colleagues.

677
00:46:11,414 --> 00:46:14,876
There are countless loan company cases
that Detective Kim has covered up.

678
00:46:17,587 --> 00:46:19,214
At this point, he's not much of a cop.

679
00:46:20,590 --> 00:46:22,509
He's more of a goon for Heaven Capital.

680
00:46:24,427 --> 00:46:27,097
Mi-kyung, this Detective Kim.

681
00:46:27,222 --> 00:46:30,266
Remember the traffic accident
on the riverside road?

682
00:46:30,350 --> 00:46:32,894
Can you find out
if he was dispatched for it?

683
00:46:33,436 --> 00:46:34,771
How do you know about that?

684
00:46:35,605 --> 00:46:38,858
He's usually always slacking off.

685
00:46:38,942 --> 00:46:43,696
I thought it was strange
when he said he wanted to go.

686
00:46:43,780 --> 00:46:47,784
Ah, this might be easier than I thought.

687
00:46:48,410 --> 00:46:50,745
I'll go meet with Detective Kim tomorrow.

688
00:46:50,829 --> 00:46:52,288
You will?

689
00:46:54,416 --> 00:46:55,625
Recognize this place?

690
00:46:57,252 --> 00:46:59,421
Yeah, isn't this where Yoo In-gu held me?

691
00:46:59,504 --> 00:47:02,757
That's right. Yeongseon Food.
This is their base of operations.

692
00:47:03,258 --> 00:47:06,261
They package it to look like preservatives
and put it in their beef jerky.

693
00:47:06,344 --> 00:47:08,680
Then they distribute it nationwide
from Yeongseon Island.

694
00:47:09,180 --> 00:47:12,934
The day after tomorrow,
a huge drug shipment from China

695
00:47:13,017 --> 00:47:15,979
is coming into Yeongseon Island
through Yeongseon Port.

696
00:47:16,729 --> 00:47:18,440
So they're bringing it in
disguised as cargo?

697
00:47:19,274 --> 00:47:21,943
Word on the street is that the Ingu Sect
poured all their funds into this.

698
00:47:22,444 --> 00:47:27,031
We haven't confirmed that the drug money
is to go into Han Gyeong-wook's pocket.

699
00:47:27,115 --> 00:47:28,658
But still, if we stop this...

700
00:47:28,741 --> 00:47:32,495
- We can finish Yoo In-gu for good.
- Exactly.

701
00:47:33,288 --> 00:47:37,000
- You're tracking their movements, right?
- Oh, I was about to bring that up.

702
00:47:37,083 --> 00:47:40,378
Those bastards tried to go after
someone named Kim Seon-jung.

703
00:47:40,462 --> 00:47:41,504
Kim Seon-jung?

704
00:47:41,588 --> 00:47:44,424
Yes, he's Han Gyeong-wook's rival
in the mayoral election.

705
00:47:45,216 --> 00:47:47,552
He seems to have
nothing to do with the deal.

706
00:47:47,635 --> 00:47:49,387
So I'm not sure of their plan.

707
00:47:49,471 --> 00:47:52,640
Yesterday, they were even tailing a woman
who visited Kim Seon-jung's house.

708
00:47:53,224 --> 00:47:56,227
I chased them because I thought
they were about to do something.

709
00:47:56,311 --> 00:47:57,770
And I took them down.

710
00:47:57,854 --> 00:47:58,855
Did you see her face?

711
00:47:58,938 --> 00:48:02,859
Well, she got away
while I was dealing with those goons.

712
00:48:03,610 --> 00:48:05,653
But I did get her license plate.

713
00:48:06,362 --> 00:48:09,866
The Kim Seon-jung situation
doesn't seem to be related to this deal.

714
00:48:09,949 --> 00:48:12,118
So take the plate number and
look into it later.

715
00:48:12,202 --> 00:48:13,286
Okay.

716
00:48:13,369 --> 00:48:16,372
You keep tracking Yoo In-gu's movements
related to the deal.

717
00:48:16,456 --> 00:48:17,499
Got it.

718
00:48:17,582 --> 00:48:19,876
What about Prosecutor Gang?

719
00:48:19,959 --> 00:48:21,377
I know a man carried her

720
00:48:21,461 --> 00:48:23,755
and he entered the redevelopment area.

721
00:48:23,838 --> 00:48:25,465
But they've disappeared since then.

722
00:48:25,548 --> 00:48:27,550
There's no CCTV there, either.

723
00:48:27,634 --> 00:48:31,054
Damn. If only we had Prosecutor Gang,
this would be so much easier.

724
00:48:32,055 --> 00:48:34,724
- Anyway, keep looking into it.
- Okay.

725
00:48:35,892 --> 00:48:36,893
Oh, and you.

726
00:48:40,396 --> 00:48:41,689
Gang Beom-ryong.

727
00:48:44,692 --> 00:48:45,985
Gang Beom-ryong!

728
00:48:46,611 --> 00:48:49,364
- Hey.
- What? Why?

729
00:48:51,032 --> 00:48:53,701
- What?
- What do you think?

730
00:48:55,453 --> 00:48:56,704
About what?

731
00:48:57,413 --> 00:49:00,124
Don't you have any idea
what Yoo In-gu's next move will be?

732
00:49:01,209 --> 00:49:05,255
He used to work for you.
You must know him better than anyone.

733
00:49:07,173 --> 00:49:08,675
Right.

734
00:49:10,343 --> 00:49:13,596
Why do you need my opinion?
Gong-bok already did all the research.

735
00:49:15,974 --> 00:49:17,350
Were you even listening?

736
00:49:18,601 --> 00:49:19,602
Give me a break.

737
00:49:19,686 --> 00:49:22,063
I only missed a bit
because I was thinking.

738
00:49:23,064 --> 00:49:24,732
Come on, I got the gist of it.

739
00:49:26,859 --> 00:49:30,905
We're on the verge of drugs flooding
Yeongseon Island, and you're zoning out?

740
00:49:31,614 --> 00:49:33,199
I wouldn't expect any less
from an ex-thug.

741
00:49:33,283 --> 00:49:35,660
No sense of responsibility, no passion.

742
00:49:35,743 --> 00:49:39,205
This guy, I swear.
It's always about me being a gangster.

743
00:49:39,706 --> 00:49:42,542
Hey, you think gangsters
don't have feelings?

744
00:49:43,251 --> 00:49:44,877
Ever think about a gangster's feelings?

745
00:49:46,713 --> 00:49:49,549
What? Why the hell are you getting mad?

746
00:49:50,842 --> 00:49:52,343
- Don't stop me.
- Hands off!

747
00:49:52,427 --> 00:49:53,428
I wasn't touching you.

748
00:49:58,099 --> 00:49:59,309
Hey, what's gotten into you?

749
00:50:03,855 --> 00:50:05,648
Look, I got the gist of it.

750
00:50:05,732 --> 00:50:08,985
So if you need anything from me,
just tell Gong-bok.

751
00:50:09,068 --> 00:50:11,529
I've got things to do at the store,
so I'm off.

752
00:50:16,242 --> 00:50:19,704
- Beom-ryong!
- What was that about?

753
00:50:21,748 --> 00:50:22,749
Beom-ryong.

754
00:50:23,708 --> 00:50:24,751
Get home safe.

755
00:50:26,127 --> 00:50:30,048
- I'm sorry. I got a little carried away.
- Nothing to be sorry about.

756
00:50:30,131 --> 00:50:31,257
Still...

757
00:50:32,258 --> 00:50:34,510
You seem really stressed out.

758
00:50:37,430 --> 00:50:39,474
So that's why he's acting like this?

759
00:50:39,557 --> 00:50:42,060
Because of that cop he had a crush on?

760
00:50:42,143 --> 00:50:45,021
Yes, he said nothing's
going on between them.

761
00:50:45,104 --> 00:50:47,106
But ever since her visit,
he's been like that.

762
00:50:49,275 --> 00:50:50,610
That's not good.

763
00:50:50,693 --> 00:50:53,488
- Why's that?
- We're moving in tomorrow.

764
00:50:54,405 --> 00:50:55,823
He could sabotage the whole thing.

765
00:50:55,907 --> 00:50:59,327
Come on, Beom-ryong was a legend
in the Hwasan Sect.

766
00:50:59,410 --> 00:51:02,372
You think he'd mess up a job
over some trouble with a girl?

767
00:51:02,497 --> 00:51:07,085
So you're sure Gang Beom-ryong
will be over that woman by tomorrow?

768
00:51:08,086 --> 00:51:11,422
Do you think your boss is
that rational and level-headed?

769
00:51:11,964 --> 00:51:13,132
No, not at all.

770
00:51:15,551 --> 00:51:19,180
Tell me everything you know
about Gang Beom-ryong.

771
00:51:26,604 --> 00:51:28,481
Hey, Mi-kyung. Get over here.

772
00:51:30,400 --> 00:51:31,818
Hurry up and get over here.

773
00:51:34,112 --> 00:51:37,699
Why do you keep sticking your nose
where it doesn't belong?

774
00:51:37,824 --> 00:51:40,743
You think all cops are the same?
There are ranks, you know.

775
00:51:40,827 --> 00:51:43,454
You barely got that ID around your neck
at your age.

776
00:51:43,538 --> 00:51:45,748
You should learn to stay in your lane.

777
00:51:45,832 --> 00:51:49,335
Ugh, this is so frustrating.
How'd you even get in?

778
00:51:50,503 --> 00:51:52,505
Get your shit together.

779
00:52:04,600 --> 00:52:06,269
- Turning yourself in?
- Jesus!

780
00:52:07,979 --> 00:52:10,398
Hey, what's your deal?

781
00:52:10,481 --> 00:52:12,108
How did you know I'd be here?

782
00:52:13,401 --> 00:52:15,486
You look right at home.

783
00:52:15,945 --> 00:52:17,280
- What?
- Yeah.

784
00:52:17,363 --> 00:52:20,408
Turning yourself in wouldn't be
that terrible of an idea.

785
00:52:20,491 --> 00:52:22,493
It's one way to repent
for all that you've done.

786
00:52:23,995 --> 00:52:25,121
But that's not it, is it?

787
00:52:25,788 --> 00:52:27,999
Why are you staring at the station
so wistfully?

788
00:52:29,083 --> 00:52:31,169
It's because of that cop from earlier,
isn't it?

789
00:52:32,295 --> 00:52:35,798
- Who?
- She's way out of your league.

790
00:52:35,923 --> 00:52:37,592
Don't you think
you're in two different films?

791
00:52:37,675 --> 00:52:41,387
She's romance, you're crime thriller.
You don't match at all.

792
00:52:41,471 --> 00:52:43,973
If you ask me,
a store owner and a regular.

793
00:52:44,056 --> 00:52:45,767
Thta's the best you can hope for.

794
00:52:47,101 --> 00:52:48,478
- Did Gong-bok talk again?
- Yep.

795
00:52:49,687 --> 00:52:50,688
Leave me alone.

796
00:52:50,772 --> 00:52:52,482
It's not what you
and Gong-bok are worried about.

797
00:52:52,940 --> 00:52:55,985
- I didn't come this way over Mi-kyung.
- Then what?

798
00:52:56,652 --> 00:52:58,404
Why are you here at such a critical time?

799
00:52:59,906 --> 00:53:01,073
Gang Beom-ryong.

800
00:53:01,616 --> 00:53:03,826
- Don't you know what's important?
- I know.

801
00:53:03,910 --> 00:53:05,286
What do you know?

802
00:53:05,369 --> 00:53:09,415
- I want to end this so badly!
- I packed a bag and left my home!

803
00:53:14,545 --> 00:53:17,715
Tomorrow's operation will be hard
even if we're at our 100%.

804
00:53:17,799 --> 00:53:20,468
If you juggle everything at once,
you'll end up dropping it all.

805
00:53:20,551 --> 00:53:22,386
Whether it's Yoo In-gu or Han Gyeong-wook

806
00:53:22,470 --> 00:53:25,556
we gotta finish this so you can go back
to the life you want, right?

807
00:53:26,474 --> 00:53:28,684
So stop getting distracted
and focus on the task.

808
00:53:29,393 --> 00:53:32,980
Asking her out and getting turned down
can wait until the job is done.

809
00:53:34,732 --> 00:53:36,526
I know that.
Don't act like you know everything.

810
00:53:37,485 --> 00:53:40,613
Once this is all over,
I'll go and talk to her for real!

811
00:53:43,074 --> 00:53:47,203
But the way I see it,
I don't think you have a shot.

812
00:53:47,286 --> 00:53:51,123
That's ridiculous.
Gong-bok said Mi-kyung is into me too.

813
00:53:51,207 --> 00:53:53,793
You believe that?
I bet he was just being nice.

814
00:53:53,876 --> 00:53:55,795
Does he look like he cares about me?

815
00:53:55,878 --> 00:53:58,965
But still.
What will you do if she turns you down?

816
00:54:03,135 --> 00:54:05,972
What, is this it? There's nothing.

817
00:54:06,055 --> 00:54:09,767
Sir, Kkot-nim and I have been
watching him like a hawk.

818
00:54:09,851 --> 00:54:13,896
But not a single soul came near the place.
He's very meticulous.

819
00:54:15,815 --> 00:54:19,151
- Did you tail him?
- Just his office and his regular diner.

820
00:54:19,235 --> 00:54:21,612
- He meets no one privately.
- Screw it.

821
00:54:22,488 --> 00:54:26,200
We'd never find any dirt on him
even if we looked for months.

822
00:54:26,325 --> 00:54:29,662
If a guy is this clean,
even Chairman Do won't find anything.

823
00:54:30,288 --> 00:54:33,291
It is a shame
I couldn't outdo him this time, though.

824
00:54:34,333 --> 00:54:38,087
I'll settle for sitting back
and watching him get an earful.

825
00:54:38,754 --> 00:54:42,967
Let's drop this and focus on our deal.
You know what I mean?

826
00:54:43,801 --> 00:54:44,802
Yes, sir.

827
00:54:48,806 --> 00:54:52,476
Besides that woman, no one else has been
in or out of Kim Seon-jung's house.

828
00:54:52,602 --> 00:54:56,314
- Did you ID this woman?
- She's definitely no ordinary woman.

829
00:54:56,981 --> 00:55:01,402
Just as we were about to grab her,
some guy appeared.

830
00:55:02,194 --> 00:55:03,988
He totally ambushed us.

831
00:55:05,156 --> 00:55:07,909
It's obvious she has someone
watching her back.

832
00:55:07,992 --> 00:55:10,995
- Watching her back?
- But take a look here.

833
00:55:11,078 --> 00:55:13,164
- Right.
- Yes, right there.

834
00:55:13,623 --> 00:55:14,665
I got a picture of the plate.

835
00:55:17,960 --> 00:55:20,796
And you're sure Yoo knows
nothing about this woman?

836
00:55:20,922 --> 00:55:22,423
Oh, yes. I haven't told him a thing.

837
00:55:23,215 --> 00:55:26,719
So for now, he's going to
stop worrying about Kim Seon-jung

838
00:55:26,802 --> 00:55:28,429
and focus on the deal.

839
00:55:30,056 --> 00:55:31,140
Okay, okay.

840
00:55:31,891 --> 00:55:34,685
Let's make sure we keep it that way.

841
00:55:34,810 --> 00:55:37,313
Don't let him get distracted
by pointless things. Okay?

842
00:55:37,396 --> 00:55:38,397
Yes, sir.

843
00:55:38,481 --> 00:55:41,150
You can go.
You must be busy with the upcoming deal.

844
00:55:41,233 --> 00:55:42,234
Yes, sir.

845
00:55:49,700 --> 00:55:52,328
Kim Seon-jung...

846
00:55:52,411 --> 00:55:53,913
Seems like there's a new variable.

847
00:55:53,996 --> 00:55:55,998
Should we revise the Kim Seon-jung plan?

848
00:55:56,457 --> 00:55:57,500
No, no.

849
00:55:57,583 --> 00:55:59,877
For now, let's stick with our plan.

850
00:55:59,961 --> 00:56:02,630
No point in flipping a table
that's already set.

851
00:56:02,713 --> 00:56:04,924
Then I'll proceed as planned.

852
00:56:05,007 --> 00:56:07,426
Wait. It can't hurt to be cautious.

853
00:56:08,427 --> 00:56:11,430
Run this woman's plate
and find out who she is.

854
00:56:11,514 --> 00:56:12,848
You said she's no ordinary woman.

855
00:56:13,474 --> 00:56:16,811
We need to see if she'll affect our plan.

856
00:56:16,894 --> 00:56:20,106
- We should at least check.
- Yes, understood.

857
00:56:27,488 --> 00:56:30,449
Man, the flame is too low.

858
00:56:35,913 --> 00:56:37,873
Why is this so tough?

859
00:56:38,666 --> 00:56:42,503
This's cheap beef.
Are you passing it off as prime grade?

860
00:56:42,586 --> 00:56:44,380
Please, just go.

861
00:56:44,463 --> 00:56:47,425
You're disturbing my business
when you're eating for free.

862
00:56:47,508 --> 00:56:49,427
Don't go making false accusations.

863
00:56:49,510 --> 00:56:50,720
When did I disturb your business?

864
00:56:51,595 --> 00:56:54,140
I mean, this is just awful.

865
00:56:54,223 --> 00:56:55,391
So tough.

866
00:56:55,474 --> 00:56:57,268
The meat here is tough!

867
00:56:57,893 --> 00:57:00,896
Here's your money, so please.

868
00:57:00,980 --> 00:57:02,690
Please, just go. Okay?

869
00:57:02,773 --> 00:57:05,234
See, was that so hard?

870
00:57:05,609 --> 00:57:07,903
Why'd you have to make things difficult?

871
00:57:07,987 --> 00:57:09,196
You're a cop.

872
00:57:09,905 --> 00:57:11,073
Don't you know this is wrong?

873
00:57:11,657 --> 00:57:12,992
But it's not.

874
00:57:13,075 --> 00:57:14,160
Look, lady.

875
00:57:14,243 --> 00:57:17,455
Don't you see those shops getting
shut down by Heaven Capital?

876
00:57:17,580 --> 00:57:20,583
And who's letting you stay in business?
It's all thanks to me.

877
00:57:21,125 --> 00:57:22,960
What's the point of me working all day?

878
00:57:23,544 --> 00:57:27,506
If you keep taking all my money,
how am I supposed to survive?

879
00:57:28,257 --> 00:57:29,258
Lady.

880
00:57:30,051 --> 00:57:32,470
You should just work harder.

881
00:57:32,553 --> 00:57:34,013
I believe in you!

882
00:57:34,638 --> 00:57:36,974
Stop annoying me
and get me some beef to go.

883
00:57:37,058 --> 00:57:38,517
For my family.

884
00:57:38,601 --> 00:57:39,977
Hurry, hurry, hurry.

885
00:57:51,197 --> 00:57:52,198
What the hell?

886
00:57:52,281 --> 00:57:53,616
What are you doing here?

887
00:57:54,283 --> 00:57:55,618
I'm on patrol.

888
00:57:55,910 --> 00:57:56,952
Patrol?

889
00:57:58,412 --> 00:57:59,413
What patrol?

890
00:58:07,129 --> 00:58:08,672
Looking for thugs like you.

891
00:58:10,925 --> 00:58:13,135
What? Park Mi-kyung,
are you out of your mind?

892
00:58:13,219 --> 00:58:16,097
You're the one who's out of your mind.
Not Officer Park.

893
00:58:16,180 --> 00:58:18,516
- What? Who are you?
- I'm so disappointed.

894
00:58:19,517 --> 00:58:21,852
I thought you were
desperately looking for me.

895
00:58:21,936 --> 00:58:23,187
You don't even recognize me?

896
00:58:24,605 --> 00:58:26,774
What are you saying? Who are you?

897
00:58:26,857 --> 00:58:27,858
Me?

898
00:58:27,942 --> 00:58:29,568
Well, Sergeant Kim.

899
00:58:29,652 --> 00:58:32,446
I'm the one you're dying to find
in Yeongseon River.

900
00:58:33,322 --> 00:58:34,573
Prosecutor Gang Yeong-ae.

901
00:58:35,783 --> 00:58:38,577
What? Don't be ridiculous.

902
00:58:39,328 --> 00:58:40,663
You went to great lengths.

903
00:58:41,372 --> 00:58:45,668
To make it look like a simple accident.

904
00:58:45,751 --> 00:58:48,003
Once you've served your time
for destroying evidence, you'll know.

905
00:58:48,087 --> 00:58:49,797
Whether I'm just a ghost...

906
00:58:50,714 --> 00:58:52,133
or Gang Yeong-ae.

907
00:58:58,430 --> 00:59:00,432
- What are you doing here?
- I was just worried.

908
00:59:19,869 --> 00:59:20,870
Are you okay?

909
00:59:35,467 --> 00:59:36,510
Are you okay?

910
00:59:51,734 --> 00:59:53,235
MY CASH COW 2

911
00:59:55,779 --> 00:59:57,656
Pick up your damn phone, will you?

912
00:59:57,740 --> 01:00:00,326
Sorry, I was in the middle of something.

913
01:00:00,409 --> 01:00:02,161
What's going on, boss?

914
01:00:02,244 --> 01:00:04,788
What do you think?
The shipment from China is tomorrow.

915
01:00:04,872 --> 01:00:09,293
- Didn't I tell you to prepare?
- Oh, yes. I remember.

916
01:00:11,670 --> 01:00:15,966
Anyway, make sure no cops
are sniffing around Yeongseon Port.

917
01:00:16,550 --> 01:00:19,470
And check for suspicious people
like that Martial Arts Master.

918
01:00:19,553 --> 01:00:20,888
Make sure to make your rounds.

919
01:00:20,971 --> 01:00:23,015
- Yes, of course, sir.
- Okay.

920
01:00:25,643 --> 01:00:26,644
Sergeant Kim.

921
01:00:28,729 --> 01:00:30,940
Looks like we have a lot to talk about.

922
01:00:35,694 --> 01:00:36,737
Mr. Bong.

923
01:00:37,446 --> 01:00:38,822
- Yes?
- Can you get up now?

924
01:00:39,323 --> 01:00:40,532
Yes, I'm good.

925
01:00:46,664 --> 01:00:48,249
Just a...

926
01:00:52,336 --> 01:00:54,755
Jang Yeong-gi,
Nampo Police, Narcotics Unit 2.

927
01:00:54,838 --> 01:00:56,006
Guess who?

928
01:00:58,926 --> 01:01:01,262
Why'd you call here?
You should've just called my cell.

929
01:01:01,387 --> 01:01:03,055
You're no fun.

930
01:01:03,138 --> 01:01:04,932
Never mind. I'll explain later.

931
01:01:05,015 --> 01:01:06,809
Yeong-gi.

932
01:01:06,892 --> 01:01:10,354
- Want to make a big bust?
- Why? What's up?

933
01:01:10,437 --> 01:01:12,314
Something really big just came up.

934
01:01:12,773 --> 01:01:14,858
I'm on Yeongseon Island.
Come over here tomorrow.

935
01:01:14,942 --> 01:01:16,568
It's been a while
since we worked together.

936
01:01:16,652 --> 01:01:17,653
Boss.

937
01:01:17,736 --> 01:01:20,072
You quit being a cop
and worked so hard to get that job.

938
01:01:20,155 --> 01:01:22,074
You should be doing desk work.

939
01:01:22,157 --> 01:01:24,368
Why are you still
running around the field?

940
01:01:24,451 --> 01:01:27,288
Hey, since when have you been so stuck up?

941
01:01:28,664 --> 01:01:30,124
Is that how I taught you?

942
01:01:30,207 --> 01:01:32,167
I'm just worried about you.

943
01:01:33,419 --> 01:01:34,628
Fine, what is it?

944
01:01:37,006 --> 01:01:39,383
-Hey, thanks for lending me your phone.
-Oh, sure.

945
01:01:39,466 --> 01:01:40,759
Did the call go well?

946
01:01:40,843 --> 01:01:42,177
Detectives will be here tomorrow.

947
01:01:45,806 --> 01:01:47,433
- Are you feeling okay?
- I will be.

948
01:01:47,516 --> 01:01:48,934
I'm still a little tingly, though.

949
01:01:58,736 --> 01:02:00,654
I think I have to get back now.

950
01:02:00,738 --> 01:02:03,073
What should I do with him?
Should I just lock him up?

951
01:02:03,157 --> 01:02:05,868
You can't lock me up! I'm innocent!

952
01:02:08,620 --> 01:02:11,457
No. Let's bring him with us for now.

953
01:02:15,836 --> 01:02:17,713
Those Ingu Sect bastards.

954
01:02:17,796 --> 01:02:19,965
I thought it was strange
how quiet they've been.

955
01:02:21,508 --> 01:02:24,428
I think they're using high school kids
from Yeongseon as human shields.

956
01:02:24,511 --> 01:02:27,389
Using high schoolers in a drug deal?
That's insane.

957
01:02:27,514 --> 01:02:30,017
Exactly. Even gangs usually have rules.

958
01:02:30,100 --> 01:02:33,020
Geum Kang-sik alone has met
with 20 to 30 high school students.

959
01:02:33,103 --> 01:02:35,147
They think it's just a high-paying job.

960
01:02:35,230 --> 01:02:37,441
It'll get complicated
with too many people.

961
01:02:37,983 --> 01:02:40,652
And we can't just mess with
these kids who know nothing.

962
01:02:43,072 --> 01:02:45,741
We'll find a way.

963
01:02:51,038 --> 01:02:52,373
This is a guy named Baek.

964
01:02:52,456 --> 01:02:54,583
A specialist in smuggling
and illegal immigration.

965
01:02:55,292 --> 01:02:59,630
He bribed officials at Yeongseon Port
and set up an office for his smuggling op.

966
01:02:59,922 --> 01:03:02,424
No one smuggles anything into
or out of Yeongseon without him.

967
01:03:03,217 --> 01:03:05,969
Same with Yoo In-gu's drugs tomorrow.

968
01:03:06,053 --> 01:03:07,930
Baek is the one accommodating it.

969
01:03:08,013 --> 01:03:11,600
We just have to secure the location
and set it up perfectly.

970
01:03:11,683 --> 01:03:13,352
we definitely have a fighting chance.

971
01:03:14,436 --> 01:03:16,355
Is that even possible?

972
01:03:17,356 --> 01:03:18,482
What's our objective?

973
01:03:18,565 --> 01:03:22,736
Even if we report the drugs,
Yoo and Han will obviously find a way out.

974
01:03:22,820 --> 01:03:25,447
And it's not like
we can take down all their men.

975
01:03:25,531 --> 01:03:27,741
But if we're just trying
to screw Yoo In-gu over?

976
01:03:28,367 --> 01:03:31,537
If that's our only objective,
then it's not impossible.

977
01:03:34,540 --> 01:03:38,085
I'm starting to see the picture.
So, what should we do first?

978
01:03:38,168 --> 01:03:41,004
- You and Gong-bok can set up the stage.
- With Gong-bok?

979
01:03:43,382 --> 01:03:46,176
- You think a civilian can pull it off?
- Hey, I can do anything.

980
01:03:46,260 --> 01:03:47,261
Just you watch.

981
01:03:52,349 --> 01:03:53,642
Okay, so what about me?

982
01:03:54,726 --> 01:03:56,895
- Should I be on standby?
- You're with me.

983
01:03:57,604 --> 01:03:58,814
We're securing the location.

984
01:04:01,150 --> 01:04:03,902
- Not confident going alone?
- I could go by myself.

985
01:04:03,986 --> 01:04:07,114
I just thought
I'd give you something to do.

986
01:04:07,197 --> 01:04:08,490
So shut up and follow my lead.

987
01:04:09,825 --> 01:04:11,827
- Fine. When are we going?
- Now.

988
01:04:13,120 --> 01:04:14,413
Hey, Kim.

989
01:04:15,831 --> 01:04:16,999
Geez.

990
01:04:17,082 --> 01:04:18,750
Is this your first day in business?

991
01:04:20,169 --> 01:04:23,922
The goods will be transported safely.

992
01:04:24,047 --> 01:04:26,592
- Don't worry. Just buy me a drink.
- Hey, boys!

993
01:04:28,927 --> 01:04:30,053
Wait, hold on.

994
01:04:30,679 --> 01:04:32,639
- What the hell?
- I don't have much time.

995
01:04:32,723 --> 01:04:34,558
So I'll keep it short.

996
01:04:34,641 --> 01:04:38,103
There's an important shipment coming in
from China tomorrow night, right?

997
01:04:38,187 --> 01:04:40,856
We need to make some adjustments
to those goods.

998
01:04:41,148 --> 01:04:44,318
So, we need to borrow your little shop
for just two days.

999
01:04:44,818 --> 01:04:48,739
Think of it as a location sponsorship.

1000
01:04:48,822 --> 01:04:50,199
What the hell?

1001
01:04:50,282 --> 01:04:53,869
What are these assholes on about?

1002
01:04:53,952 --> 01:04:56,246
Hey, what are you doing? Get 'em!

1003
01:05:02,461 --> 01:05:04,129
What are you waiting for? Get out.

1004
01:05:04,213 --> 01:05:06,048
- By myself? What about you?
- You scared?

1005
01:05:06,840 --> 01:05:08,300
Scared? Hell no.

1006
01:05:13,555 --> 01:05:16,183
SPECIAL THANKS TO
KIM SANG-KYUNG AND KWON YUL

1007
01:05:30,906 --> 01:05:33,825
Location secured. Now let's get set up.

1008
01:05:33,909 --> 01:05:35,077
Now we're real allies.

1009
01:05:37,037 --> 01:05:39,039
- Aren't you worried?
- My calculations are never off.

1010
01:05:39,122 --> 01:05:42,125
Something was definitely
going on between them.

1011
01:05:42,209 --> 01:05:44,127
- All by yourself?
- Want to come with me then?

1012
01:05:44,211 --> 01:05:46,672
- I'll do whatever.
- Be honest. Did something happen?

1013
01:05:46,797 --> 01:05:48,549
- I'm pregnant.
- Pregnant?

1014
01:05:48,632 --> 01:05:50,842
- You believe that crap?
- Shut up.

1015
01:05:50,926 --> 01:05:53,720
I know better than anyone
just how evil Han Gyeong-wook is.

1016
01:05:53,804 --> 01:05:55,722
The package is delivered.

1017
01:05:55,806 --> 01:05:58,475
If we're going to set it off,
it might as well be a good show.

1018
01:05:59,434 --> 01:06:01,562
I have to save him.
He could die if he stays there.

1019
01:06:01,645 --> 01:06:04,356
- Hey, boss!
- I was wondering when you'd show up.

1020
01:06:04,439 --> 01:06:05,732
It was you?

